					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, those are really more like registers (which <em>are</em> normally used for storing local variables, as well as anything the compiler considers temporary, really). The 65816 is quite starved on CPU registers so I imagine it's not uncommon to use a few bytes in ZP as extra &quot;registers&quot;. So, just put those starting at 0, then you pretty much ensure no variable will be ever properly assigned to those.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

